Installation Instructions

- Requires Python 3.7

Windows:
	- open setup.py in a text editor
	- for 64-bit: 
		- in the installation_requires section uncomment "PyAudio-0.2.11-cp37-cp37m-win_amd64.whl",
	- for 32-bit:
		- in the installation_requires section uncomment "PyAudio-0.2.11-cp37-cp37m-win32.whl",
	- save the file and close
	- open command prompt and cd into the root directory where setup.py is located
	- Enter the command: python setup.py install
		- If this step causes an error try to install PyAudio sepatately with the command: 
			pip install PyAudio-0.2.11-cp37-cp37m-win_amd64.whl
			- or -
			pip install PyAudio-0.2.11-cp37-cp37m-win32.whl
	- To run the server enter the command: python -m flask run
	- open a web browser and navigate to http://127.0.0.1:5000

OS X:
	- open setup.py in a text editor
	- in the installation_requires section uncomment "PyAudio==0.2.11", 
	- save the file and close
	- open terminal and cd into the root directory where setup.py is located
	- Enter the command: python setup.py install
	- To run the server enter the command: python -m flask run
	- open a web browser and navigate to http://127.0.0.1:5000
 
